Africa-Israel, Gilat, Ormat, Paz Oil: Israeli Equity Preview

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-05-08T06:30:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/africa-israel-gilat-ormat-paz-oil-israeli-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in Israeli markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after the
company names and prices are from the last close unless
otherwise stated.  The TA-25 Index lost 1.2 percent to 1,277.24 in  Tel Aviv .  Africa-Israel Investments Ltd. (AFIL)  : Richard Marin,
former chief executive officer of Africa Israel USA sued the
unit of Lev Leviev’s holding company and its Israel-based parent
to recover a $1.25 million bonus saying he was fired after
uncovering “serious instances of self-dealing and conflict of
interest.” Africa Israel dropped 1.5 percent to 27.28 shekels.  Gilat Satellite Networks Ltd. (GILT)  : The developer of
satellite network technology was chosen for an Australian
project with a potential value of as much as $120 million over
five years. Gilat declined 0.8 percent to 15.60 shekels.  Granite Hacarmel Investments Ltd. (GRNT)  : The holding
company said it stopped supplying fuel to airplanes through Paz
Oil Co. because of concern about contamination. Granite fell 2.8
percent to 6.851 shekels.  Ormat Industries (ORMT)  Ltd: The U.S. unit of the
builder and operator of geothermal was lowered to
“underperform” from “inline” at Imperial Capital LLC. Ormat
slipped 0.4 percent to 23.45 shekels.  Paz Oil Co. (PZOL IT): The energy company said it is using
fuel tankers to provide fuel for planes to take off from Ben
Gurion Airport after possible contamination was supected in its
airport tanks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Tel Aviv at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
